<HEAD>`Good Morning, Vietnam' Ties Box Office Record</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JEFF WILSON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>HOLLYWOOD (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 `` Good Morning, <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>'' was moviegoers' favorite for the the ninth-straight weekend, tying it with `` Crocodile Dundee'' for the longest consecutive time at the top Second in last weekend's box office survey was `` Vice Versa,'' featuring a Judge <PERSON> Reinhold </PERSON> transformation into a prepubescent kid, followed by `` Masquerade'' in third and `` Off Limits'' fourth. All 10 top grossing films combined took in about $ 30 million, with `` Good Morning, <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>'' ringing up a mere $ 4.36 million during the pre-Easter vacation box office doldrums. `` It's another down week,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Krier </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Exhibitor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Relations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, which surveys the studios' weekly performance at the box office. `` It looks like we're marking time until Easter.'' For the Easter break, the studios are releasing the animated feature `` The Fox and the Hounds,'' <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> Alda </PERSON>'s `` A New Life,'' <PERSON> Matthew </PERSON> <PERSON> Broderick </PERSON>'s `` Biloxi Blues'' and <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Hall </PERSON>'s `` Johnny B <PERSON> Goode </PERSON>.'' In addition to `` Good Morning, <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>,'' the <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Studios </ORGANIZATION> had two other pictures in the top 10. `` Three Men and a Baby'' was seventh 7 after 15 weeks in release and `` Shoot to Kill'' ninth. The lure of romance between <PERSON> Rob </PERSON> <PERSON> Lowe </PERSON> and <PERSON> Meg </PERSON> <PERSON> Tilly </PERSON> gave `` Masquerade'' a debut weekend gross of $ 3.5 million while the <PERSON> Willem </PERSON> <PERSON> Dafoe-Gregory </PERSON> <PERSON> Hines </PERSON> cop thriller `` Off Limits'' earned $ 2.8 million. In fifth was <PERSON> Cher </PERSON>'s critically-acclaimed `` Moonstruck,'' which won her a <ORGANIZATION> Golden </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Globe </ORGANIZATION> trophy and an Oscar nomination, followed by <PERSON> Harrison </PERSON> <PERSON> Ford </PERSON>'s `` Frantic'' in sixth and `` Three Men and a Baby'' in seventh. `` Moving,'' starring <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Pryor </PERSON> as a <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> engineer forced to relocate his family to <LOCATION> Boise </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Idaho </LOCATION>, earned more than $ 2.4 million to place eighth, followed by `` Shoot to Kill.'' In 10th place was `` Switching Channels,'' a broadcast version of the venerable newsroom comedy `` The Front Page.'' It earned $ 1.9 million in its second week. Here are the top films for the weekend as tallied by <ORGANIZATION> Exhibitor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Relations </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, with distributor, weekend gross, number of theater screens, average per screen, total gross, number of weeks in release and estimated production costs. 1. `` Good Morning, <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>,'' Disney-Touchstone, $ 4.36 million, 1,579 screens, $ 2,767 per screen, $ 91.5 million, 11 weeks, $ 21 million. 2. `` Vice Versa,'' <ORGANIZATION> Columbia </ORGANIZATION>, $ 4.05 million, 1,225 screens, $ 3,306 per screen, $ 4.05 million, one week, n-a. 3. `` Masquerade,'' <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION>, $ 3.5 million, 1,030 screens, $ 3,398 per screen, $ 3.5 million, one week, n-a. 4. `` Off Limits,'' 20th Century <PERSON> Fox </PERSON>, $ 2.79 million, 1,366 screens, $ 2,047 per screen, $ 2.79 million, one week, n-a. 5. `` Moonstruck,'' <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION>, $ 2.66 million, 1,155 screens, $ 2,309 per screen, $ 49.37 million, 12 weeks, $ 17 million. 6. `` Frantic,'' <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bros. </ORGANIZATION>, $ 2.60 million, 1,054 screens, $ 2,469 per screen, $ 13.2 million, two weeks, $ 20 million. 7. `` Three Men And A Baby,'' Disney-Touchstone, $ 2.55 million, 1,348 screens, $ 1,893 per screen, $ 147.6 million, 15 weeks, $ 18 million. 8. `` Moving,'' <ORGANIZATION> Warner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bros. </ORGANIZATION>, $ 2.4 million, 1,404 screens, $ 1,732 per screen, $ 7.49 million, two weeks, n-a. 9. `` Shoot to Kill,'' Disney-Touchstone, $ 2 million, 1,037 screens, $ 1,956 per screen, $ 24.2 million, four weeks, $ 18 million. 10. `` Switching Channels,'' Tri-Star, $ 1.94 million, 971 screens, $ 2,002 per screen, $ 5.8 million, two weeks, n-a.
