unrest in the occupied lands, <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> stepped up economic sanctions. Shipment of gasoline and other fuel to service stations in the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> was banned as of Sunday. According to <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> figures, at least 91 Palestinians have been killed since anti-Israeli rioting began Dec. 8.
