 guilt. I'm at peace with myself, with the world, with each of you. God bless you.'' <PERSON> Darden </PERSON> winked and nodded at one of his attorneys just before the hood was put over his head, and was declared dead at 7:12 a.m. after 2,000 volts of electricity flowed through his body for two minutes. Two puffs of smoke rose from his right leg where one of the electrodes was attached. On Monday, the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION>, the 11th U.S. <ORGANIZATION> Circuit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Appeals </ORGANIZATION>, a federal judge and the state <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> rejected <PERSON> Darden </PERSON>'s appeals on his seventh warrant. No inmate on <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>'s death row had ever survived more than three warrants on the same crime Before dawn Tuesday, 40 people gathered in a pasture across from the prison. The protesters maintained silence until the execution took place, then began singing `` We Shall Overcome.'' Court records say that after shooting <PERSON> Turman </PERSON>, <PERSON> Darden </PERSON> ordered his wife to perform oral sex on him while <PERSON> Turman </PERSON> lay dying a few feet away. A neighbor, <PERSON> Philip </PERSON> <PERSON> Arnold </PERSON>, also identified <PERSON> Darden </PERSON> during the trial. <PERSON> Arnold </PERSON>, then 16, entered the store after apparently hearing the shooting and the woman's cries. He was shot three times but survived. Death penalty opponents, led by <ORGANIZATION> Amnesty </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION>, have said <PERSON> Darden </PERSON> had an alibi proving his innocence. They claim statements from a minister and a woman show <PERSON> Darden </PERSON> could not have committed the murder. In <LOCATION> Sweden </LOCATION>, about a dozen people demon