ut other cities' convention center proposals. <LOCATION> Duluth </LOCATION>, a city of 85,000 on the western tip of <LOCATION> Lake </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Superior </LOCATION>, was never in competition for a $ 200 million convention center for which <LOCATION> Bloomington </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Minneapolis </LOCATION> vied, according to the charges. The Legislature awarded <LOCATION> Duluth </LOCATION> a total of $ 17.2 million for its relatively small center. Prosecutors say the mayor played a limited role in lobbying for the convention center which he later claimed to have won almost single-handedly.
