<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The stock market was unchanged in the early going today as reluctance by traders to take positions ahead of the government's upcoming release of trade data continued to dampen activity. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was unchanged at 2,050.07 at 11 a.m. on Wall Street. Losers outnumbered gainers by about 6 to 5 in the overall tally of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 673 up, 568 down and 525 unchanged in the first 90 minutes of trading. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 46,070,000 million shares. Analysts said the market fluctuated in a narrow range in the absence of any major news. `` There is a mood in the street of reluctance to make commitments'' prior to the release of January merchandise trade figures on Thursday, said <PERSON> Lew </PERSON> <PERSON> Smith </PERSON>, a technical analyst at <ORGANIZATION> Bear </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stearns </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. That sentiment that also dominated activity in the previous session `` The last two -LRB- market -RRB- responses to the trade numbers took place in a half hour'' of trading, said <PERSON> Larry </PERSON> <PERSON> Wachtel </PERSON>, first vice president at <ORGANIZATION> Prudential-Bache </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc </ORGANIZATION>. While analysts noted that the market may be overplaying the impact the figure is likely to have on Wall Street, this week's trade report will come just ahead of a quarterly `` triple witching hour'' involving a group of expiring options and futures on stock indexes The past couple of witching hours have been relatively uneventful with the adoption of new procedures designed to spread out the impact of last-minute maneuvering by computer program traders. On the actives list, airline issues were up amid reports that a number of carriers plan to tighten restrictions on discount fares. <ORGANIZATION> Allegis </ORGANIZATION> rose 1 | to 79 -LCB-, <ORGANIZATION> AMR </ORGANIZATION> rose 1 | to 42 |, and <ORGANIZATION> Southwest </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> was up -RRB- <ORGANIZATION> Federated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stores </ORGANIZATION> fell -RRB- to 65 | as <PERSON> Macy </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> continue to battle for control of the retial giant <ORGANIZATION> Grolier </ORGANIZATION> was up -LRB- to 24 -LCB-. Paris-based <ORGANIZATION> Hachette </ORGANIZATION> filed suit in federal court challenging <ORGANIZATION> Grolier </ORGANIZATION>'s poison pill. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks fell 0.10 to 149.96. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was down 0.08 at 296.86.
