ross the board amid reports that a number of carriers plan to tighten restrictions on discount fares. <ORGANIZATION> Allegis </ORGANIZATION> rose 1 -RRB- to 79 |, <ORGANIZATION> AMR </ORGANIZATION> rose 1 -RRB- to 42 -RRB-, <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> was up 1 -RRB- to 47 |, and <ORGANIZATION> NWA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> was up ~ to 43 First RepublicBank fell -LCB- to 1 \ amid reports that it will seek a federal bailout It is <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>' largest bank holding company. Traders complained that the technology sector failed to help establish a positive trend for the day. <ORGANIZATION> Digital </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Equipment </ORGANIZATION> fell 2 -LCB- to 116 \ and <ORGANIZATION> IBM </ORGANIZATION> was down 1 | to <ORGANIZATION> Federated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stores </ORGANIZATION> fell \ to 65 -RCB- as <PERSON> Macy </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Campeau </ORGANIZATION> continue to battle for control of the retail giant. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks fell 0.21 to 149.85. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was down 0.67 at 296.27.
