<HEAD>NHTSA Opens Acceleration Probe of Honda Acura Legend, Austin Rover
Sterling</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDs: CORRECTS 9th graf, bgng: Typically Acura, to show that motor
races when shifted into drive or reverse, sted park or reverse;
also moved on general news wires</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By TIM BOVEE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Nearly 150 complaints of sudden acceleration have prompted the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Highway </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Traffic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> to open an investigation of the <ORGANIZATION> Honda </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Acura </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Legend </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Austin </PERSON> <PERSON> Rover </PERSON> <PERSON> Sterling </PERSON>. The agency said Monday the investigation covers 62,500 1986-1988 Acura Legends and <PERSON> Austin </PERSON> <PERSON> Rover </PERSON> <PERSON> Sterlings </PERSON> with automatic shifts. The Austin Rover Sterling uses the same mechanical components as the Legend. The new investigation brings to seven the number of sudden acceleration probes being conducted by <ORGANIZATION> NHTSA </ORGANIZATION>. Five of the investigations involve imported vehicles. American <ORGANIZATION> Honda </ORGANIZATION>, through spokesman <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Butorac </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Gardena </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, declined to comment specifically on the <ORGANIZATION> NHTSA </ORGANIZATION> investigation, saying it would be inappropriate `` because we simply have n't heard anything yet.'' `` We've checked every vehicle in which that incident -LRB- sudden acceleration -RRB- was reported, -LRB- and -RRB- never found any mechanical or electrical defect that could have caused it,'' <PERSON> Butorac </PERSON> said. He declined to say what could have brought on the sudden acceleration incidents in the absence of a mechanical or electrical cause. <ORGANIZATION> NHTSA </ORGANIZATION> has received 147 complaints of sudden acceleration in the cars, resulting in 82 accidents, 11 injuries and no fatalities. The Center for Auto Safety, a Washington-based public-issues group, had petitioned <ORGANIZATION> NHTSA </ORGANIZATION> to open an engineering analysis of the alleged throttle problems. Typically, Acura Legend owners report their cars idle normally in park, but race out of control when shifted into either drive or reverse, said the center, a private organization often at odds with the auto industry and its regulators. <ORGANIZATION> NHTSA </ORGANIZATION> has conducted three investigations into another <ORGANIZATION> Honda </ORGANIZATION> model, the Accord, without ordering a recall, the center said. The center said it has reports of at least 120 Accord sudden acceleration accidents resulting in three deaths. <ORGANIZATION> Honda </ORGANIZATION> recalled 4,500 of its 1988 Civics in November because of speed fluctuation when the cars were idling, the center said.
