<HEAD>Desert Partners Mounts Proxy Fight for Directors' Seats</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIDLAND, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Desert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> L.P. </ORGANIZATION> has begun a soliciting proxies from shareholders for the election of directorships of <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, which recently spurned an unsolicited $ 1.9 billion buyout offer from the investor group. Desert Partners, the company's largest shareholder with 9.8 percent of the stock, is fielding a rival slate for the six seats at stake in the upcoming election. USG has 15 directors. Earlier this month, <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION> rejected <ORGANIZATION> Desert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>' $ 42-a-share buyout offer and said it was considering defense strategies that might include the sale of a major block of <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION> stock to a third party to block an unfriendly takeover. The proxy battle by <ORGANIZATION> Desert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>, which is headed by <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION> oilmen <PERSON> Jack </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> and <PERSON> Cyril </PERSON> <PERSON> Wagner </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, will climax May 11 at <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION>'s annual meeting in its headquarters city of <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> USG </ORGANIZATION>'s stock closed at $ 35.87 -LCB- a share, down 25 cents in <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> trading. Desert Partners said in its proxy statement that even if it wins all six seats, it still would not control the building materials company. `` However, a vote in favor of the election of the Desert Partners nominees should indicate your support for the offer,'' the proxy statement read. Shareholders will receive two proxy statements, one from the company and the other from <ORGANIZATION> Desert </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>.
